
[1]inflammatory

   INFLAM'MATORY, a. Inflaming; tending to excite heat or inflammation; as
   medicines of an inflammatory nature.

   1. Accompanied with preternatural heat and excitement of arterial
   action; as an inflammatory fever or disease.

   2. Tending to excite anger, animosity, tumult or sedition; as
   inflammatory libels, writings, speeches or publications.
